    "question_stem": "A circle and a straight line are defined by the following equations:",
    "parts": [
        {
            "part_label": "a",
            "question_text": "Find the coordinates of the points where the line and the circle intersect.",
            "solution_text": "We are given the equations \\(x + y = 6\\) and \\(x^2 + y^2 = 20\\). Rearrange the linear equation to express \\(y\\) in terms of \\(x\\): \\(y = 6 - x\\).\nSubstitute this expression for \\(y\\) into the equation of the circle:\n\\(x^2 + (6 - x)^2 = 20\\)\n\\(x^2 + 36 - 12x + x^2 = 20\\)\n\\(2x^2 - 12x + 16 = 0\\)\nDivide by 2:\n\\(x^2 - 6x + 8 = 0\\)\nFactorise:\n\\((x - 2)(x - 4) = 0\\)\nSo, \\(x = 2\\) or \\(x = 4\\).\nWhen \\(x = 2\\), \\(y = 6 - 2 = 4\\). When \\(x = 4\\), \\(y = 6 - 4 = 2\\).\nTherefore, the points of intersection are \\((2, 4)\\) and \\((4, 2)\\)."
        }
